This move I'm not sure about.. I don't see how white garner's any advantage from moving his rook out. White's queen needs to take a more offensive role, the only thing it's doing is protecting the knight when there is no piece on the board that can threaten it. I think Qe3 is a better move because it protects the bishop and at least threatens Qa7.

This is the misstep which costs white the game. Ne4 would have been better.. that threatens the queen and white needs to get his knight to the other side of the board.. as it that spot where his attack needs to go. White I suspect thought that he could win back the pawn.. Qxg5.. Rxe5.. forcing the queen to retreat and then equalizing material with Rxe6. What he didn't see however is c3 is exposed and the consequences of a highly mobile queen.
